radiographic_examinations.findings: Very minimal bilateral dependent atelectasis; unremarkable liver, gallbladder, spleen, pancreas, adrenal glands, and kidneys; no hydronephrosis bilaterally; collapsed stomach; no bowel obstruction; dilated appendix measuring up to 12 mm in diameter, fluid-filled with thickened wall; moderate periappendiceal fat stranding; scattered colonic diverticula; small amount of free fluid in pelvis; 1.5 cm right corpus luteal cyst; mild sclerosis at sacroiliac joints; no acute fracture or dislocation.
